<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro _MHD_ROTL32 expands to ((uint32_t)__builtin_rotateleft32((value32),(bits))). The identifier __builtin_rotateleft32 is a compiler-specific builtin (a non-standard compiler extension documented by compilers such as GCC/Clang) rather than standard C. Therefore this use constitutes a language extension and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 1.2. Replace with a portable standard-C rotation (shifts and OR) or gate the builtin behind a portability/configuration macro.
</scenario>
